Kaveel Singh, News24A taxi accident has claimed the life of a 12-year-old boy. (Rescue Care) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; A 12-year-old boy was killed when a minibus taxi knocked him down outside a park in Pinetown on Friday, paramedics said. The taxi left the road, knocked down two pedestrians, including the boy, and crashed into a swing set, Rescue Care spokesperson Garrith Jamieson said.The child&rsquo;s injuries were too severe and paramedics were unable to resuscitate him.Nine people sustained injuries, ranging from minor to moderate. They were taken to local hospitals.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.